725145f-a.text:
26th Ave., north side, east of 4th Street, showing in the center, to the east of the Weisberg-Baer sash and door factory (left),the John J. Halsey house. This house was demolished prior to 1928. A. L. Hatch
was the owner in 1891.
1922.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
